ophy and science, and of the crisis that both are undergoing today. In the end, there is no universal answer to what is an impossible or inexhaustible question, and philosophical writing-a problem Agamben has never ceased to grapple with-assumes the form of a prelude to a work that must remain unwritten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aLanguage and languagesxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh1 aChiesa, Lorenzo08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360405640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503604056423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503604056.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles